I'm not a nuclear physicist...but I believe with fission they use uranium 235 (an isotope of uranium)...basically because it's a little unstable and is easy to crack open...but fusion I can see in the future it's a lot more efficient (not at the moment though)...they can't do cold fusion yet...maybe they won't be able to...which could explain the heat...I don't believe you can fuse 2 elements to create another...I'm not too sure how fusion works though...<br>
But I could explain a bit of what I got from chemistry...first off...neutrons don't matter (excuse the pun)...except in weight...they weigh they same as protons...neutrons are what makes isotopes...protons are what determines the element...and electrons the charge (changed by gaining or loosing them)...in the normal state an element has equal numbers of all of them...<br>
Chemical reactions go like this... a + b = ab ... ab+c = ac+b...ab+cd = ad+bc<br>
(I think that's right...it's late and I'm doing it from memory...)<br>
I can imagine fusion might go something like this...you might also make a chemical reaction engine...the physics of chemistry are pretty solid but there's enough there to have fun playing with...keep in mind they're always discovering new elements...nobody is saying you cant add a couple more (gundamium)...You can make anything you like with your own stuff...maybe your fusion engine could work...just not with todays elements...maybe a chemical reaction engine could work...or maybe get really creative and have an engine that feeds off the pilot...causing pilot fatigue and problems like that in the begining but once pilot and mech become more used to each other those problems become less (the engine evolves to be more efficient)...<br>
As well if you were going to have it output titanium...it should be titanium vapor...you wouldn't have to deal with extra weight and it would make sense due to the heat...and it could fall to the planet in rain to be mined...(Mmm..titanium raindrops)...<br>
Just some random ideas...remember to be creative...in the future you can totally shake off the past and people won't hate you for it...I'm just being really nitpicky... <p>--
